 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Dalamarn Darkgem</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> First subject, try scarlet desert (stay near a zone, some will be mighty tough for you) or get in with a group at the giant fort in BW (burning woods).  Fort is at /loc 1000, 1000 .. both positive numbers.  The wasps in burning woods are summoned.  The wurms and sarnaks are regular mobs.  </P><P>NOW THE GOOD NEWS, the apes and the skeles there are undead.  If you cant get in a group at giant fort, there is are undead ruins just to the east of that giant fort with 7 spawns.  I kept it cleared EASY solo at 51 (I FLEW from 51 to 52 in a weekend and got 2 1/2 yellows in AA while doing it), but the mobs should still be doable at 46 (simple at 49+ with 49 pet).  Park your pet near the end of the logs coming from fort.. maybe a little north of them. The fear path will take mobs east and you DONT want them walking through the ruins at your level.  Pull with darkness, run to pet, sit to med till mob gets close, throw pet at him, stand up and fear immediatly (use your level 12 undead fear because it's only 10 mana.. you'll have to reapply a few times.. but who cares... it's only 10 mana).  Throw on a vampiric embrace to restore your life and apply DOTs as you prefer.. just keep him feared.  you might want to use your undead slow at that level as well, in the time it takes you to re-fear they'll be eating your pet up, so throw on the shackle of spirit after the first fear.  The higher level apes will social argo, so be careful of adds.</P><P>For the person needing the words for their level 49 spells.  Check the bazaar merchants in Luclin.  Many people sell them there.  Also have a friend check rivervale merchants for you.  Those words drop like mad off of raptors and the druids who quad kill them like to port back to rivervale to sell them.</P><P> </font></td>
