        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Dalamarn Darkgem</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Aye, bloodgills in Lake of Ill Omen are good too, fear one away, other will attack you.  Throw pet at it, darkness it and fear (it WONT go far).  They have LOW hps and are good exp.  Watch out for the fish(barracuda?) in the water.  You dont want one getting on your back while you're fighting gobbies.  You should kill the first goblin fairly quick and the second one will be coming back.  Take him and move to the next group.  In the front there is a gorup of 4, you dont want to pull all of them so be careful.  There's also a spot where a fish (barracuda?) spawns about 30 secs to 1 minute after you kill it.  They're easy like the goblins.  If someone can post the /loc it spawns at, you can continuously kill this thing almost nonstop for a few levels.  When you fear it, it'll onlly go about 5 feet, so a SIMPLE kill that you can play with for quite a while.</P><P> </font></td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Necridious</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Echo Caverns, the side that goes to the Deep.</P><P>XP is awesome here, Soloing is easy.  Money is ok.  The room outside where the taskmaster spawns has 7 easily single pulled spawns.  The Taskmaster room itself is simple if your an Iksar, the skeletons with the taskmaster won't social aggro an Iksar, and nothing will social aggro anyone 50+.  You can start soling here from 42, though untill 45 you will need to Fear Kite, as the 39 Pet just can't stand up to an Underbulk very long.</P><P>Killing any of the normal mobs outside the TM room is easy: Send in Pet with Augment Death up, Hit with Vampiric Curse, and hit pet with <i>Pact of Shadow</i>.  Sit down, and Med up for next fight. Once you know the order to kill them in, you don't even have to break the spawn.  Time it right, and you can kill nonstop forever, breaking only for rare appearances of Fireclaw and Trillcor.  Fear Pathing is also great, and you can pretty much Fear with impunity.</P><P>Your outer mobs are:</P><P><b><font size=5>Underbulk</font id=size5></b>-  Average Mob<BR>&gt;&gt;Drops pincers that sell for 3+pp each, and stack.  They are also good throwing weapons because of their range.</P><P><b><font size=5>Stonegrabbers</font id=size5></b>-  Highly resistant, especially fire, attacks slow and hard.<BR>&gt;&gt;Drops on average of 6pp per kill.</P><P><b><font size=5>Fungal Fiends</font id=size5></b>- Poison and Disease Resistant, Attack fairly fast<BR>&gt;&gt;Drop some good stat food, and some NICE throwers, better than Underbulk claws, but only sell for some silver.  I suggest saving these and making some monk happy, and selling the claws. </P><P><b><font size=5>Trillcor</font id=size5></b>  Named Fungal Fiend<BR>This thing is a pain in the butt.  He's got a Proc of Whirl till you Hurl, hard and fast damage, and plenty of Hitpoints. He can be Snared, but not Feared.  The way kill him is just to go all out.  Buff up your best Skin, Banshee Aura, DMF, Resist Disease, and whatever else you want, buff the pet, launch as many dot's as will stick, and lifetap his annoying self to death before he kills you.<BR>&gt;&gt;He rarely drops normal Fungal Fiend loot, which is why he's SO annoying.</P><P><b><font size=5>Fireclaw</font id=size5></b>  Named Underbulk<BR>Basicaly a bigger nastier version of the underbulk, he seems a bit more resistant to fire. He hits pretty hard, and fairly fast, has truckloads of HP, Procs Fireclaw {75 fire DD}, and cannot be snared. Killing him is much the same as Trillcor, only more dangerous as he has more HP and cannot be snared.<BR>&gt;&gt;The good news is that he drops Fireclaw Talons {8/26 H2H with Fireclaw Proc} and a Fireclaw Carapice {Back Slot +8 AC +5 Str +10 vsFire}</P><P>Now for the real XP, and the Money. TM room Spawns are:</P><P><b><font size=5>Taskmaster Torkzah</font id=size5></b>  Named Undead Shissar, just like the ones in the Grey.<BR>He Attacks fast and Hard, has plenty of HP, and has Moderatly good resists. However, He can be Snared and Feared if you've cleared the outer room, and he's UNDEAD.<BR>&gt;&gt;Drops:<BR>An Orb of Echo Ore {+20 HP +20 Mana  Range Slot}<i>common</i><BR>Cracked Revenant Skull <i>Every Time, has to be a quest somewhere</i><BR>A Phosphorescent Fiber {7/24 +2 Poison DMG. +5 vsPos +5 vsDis}<i>rare, vendorize for 50pp</i><BR>Shissar Organs {The ones used in the Katta EB Necklace Quest}<i>very rare</i><BR>A Scale that sells for 20pp at the merchant, but has no other use I know. Also probably a quest, it's super rare, like the organs.</P><P><b><font size=5>Iksar Slaves</font id=size5></b>  Average undead for their level, they are about as high as the named in the outer room, but easy to kill if you get them alone. anyone 50+, or an Iksar can single pull them, and there's about 6 or 7 up with the Taskmaster.  Not terribly resistant, they take well to all our undead spells. I have been in groups with up to level 54's who claimed they were great xp for them, and I know it was for me.<BR>&gt;&gt;The each drop a Pick, which sells for 7+pp. It's a crappy weapon, and to make it really annoying, Lore.  But there is a Merchant in the zone who will buy them, if you want to make the money off of them.  Over time, this is actually better cash than the Hill Giants...</P><P><b><font size=5>Xinlinov</font id=size5></b>  Undead Thought Horror<BR>This guy is what you cannot handle, gives level 60's a run for their money, and I don't want to think about him after the NPC spell casting changes.  He's a level 52 Enchanter, and really fond of Charm, Gravity Flux, and attacks REALLY fast and REALLY hard. He also takes time to buff the Taskmaster and any Skeletons that are up there when he pops.  He's very rare, I was there several days before I saw him the first time, then we killed him twice in one 4 hour period another day.  The Taskmaster is his Placeholder, and he will despawn shortly after the Taskmaster pops up again, so you can just wait him out.  Fortunatly, since you have to pass through Echo Caverns to get to the Deep, there are usually enough High levels to make him doable and are willing to give it a crack.  Have a Cleric handy though, he's no Pushover. He is Immune to fear, though not otherwise Highly resistant, I was able to land Assystole each time on the first try, though that did result in my immediate summons and execution, even at half health.<BR>&gt;&gt;Drops are:<BR>Terror Boots {+8 AC +4 Wis +4 Int +2 vsMg +2 vsFire +2 vsCold +2 vsPos +2 vsDis +10 HP +10 Mana}<BR>Terror Guantlets {AC: +12 Magic Resist: +3 Fire Resist: +3 Cold Resist: +3 Poison Resist: +3 Disease Resist: +3 HP: +2}</P><P><BR>There you go, I hope it helps.</P><P>"Know Fear through me, Not of me."</font></td>
